Pick a seedling to plant:
Tasks
Main goal: Bonsai master
Instructions:
Since being small you wanted to grow bonsais and be the best in it. Now is the time to do so!
Go out and built yourself up to be a bonsai master!
Goal:
Have the best bonsai possible.
Tutorial: Expeditions
Goal:
Obtain one seedling. Return here afterwards.
Tutorial: Plant a bonsai
Instructions:
Your first seedling, now you need to plant it. Click one of the empty bonsai spaces on the left side and plant your first bonsai.
Goal:
Plant one bonsai. Return here afterwards.
Tutorial: Bonsai species and potentials
Instructions:
One bonsai isn't enough, you're thinking to yourself. You want more tree species to grow into bonsais and maybe a seedling with a better potential of being a great bonsai.
Go back on an expedition. You can now go on longer expeditions for better chances on different tree species and potential.
Goal:
Obtain two different tree species. Return here afterwards.
Tutorial: Learn building robots
Instructions:
With all the seedlings you found, you don't know how to grow them all at the same time.
If I only would have more help, you thought.
Luckily you're handy with electronics and remember having an instruction book for building robots. You should learn how to build one.
Goal:
Learn 'Building robots'.
Tutorial: Craft a robot
Instructions:
Reading the book took some time, but finally you finished. Now it's time to build your new helper.
Go to 'Craft' and craft a robot.
Goal:
Craft a robot.
Tutorial: Bonsai growing
Instructions:
When you flick the switch, your robot beeps and looks at you.
How may I help you, he asks?
Grow together with your new robotic helper two bonsais to at least level 5.
Goal:
Two bonsais with at least level 5.
Tutorial: Compost
Instructions:
Your bonsais are growing. But it does take longer and longer, the bigger your bonsais get, you realize.
With the experience from doing expeditions and growing bonsais, I should have the skills by now to learn how to make compost and produce some, you think.
That might help them to grow quicker!
Goal:
Learn 'Compost making' and craft 3 compost.
Tutorial: Level Up Bonsai
Instructions:
With the addition of compost your bonsais are now growing quicker. Time to bring them up to the next level.
You can now add compost to bonsais when they still have to grow for 60 or more seconds, through the growing button.
Goal:
Grow a bonsai to level 10
Tutorial: Growing Skill
Instructions:
Your knowledge and skill level is slowly growing. Time to refine your skill in growing your bonsais and giving them another boost.
You can now learn "Growing #1" a skill that boosts the increase of CP with each level.
Note: CP stand for Combined Points and measure the growth of your bonsai. The higher the level and potential of a bonsai, the higher the CP can be.
Goal:
Learn "Growing #1" and grow a bonsai with 30 or more CP
Tutorial: Shopping
Instructions:
Strolling your neighborhood for new bonsais you meet a person that tells you about different bonsais on the outskirts of the city.
Time to go shopping, so that you can take an expedition there.
Note: Bonsais have type. The rarer the type the more worth the bonsai is.
Goal:
Buy the backpack
Tutorial: Shopping #2
Instructions:
Because your bonsais need more and more care you think about building another robot.
Unfortunately you don't have the resources yet, but the shop might be able to help you.
Goal:
Build a third robot
Tutorial: Shaping skill
Instructions:
One day you meet another person that grows bonsais and learn that you can not only grow bonsais, but also actively shape them.
You can now learn "Shaping #1" a skill that lets you distribute a portion of the new CP your bonsai gains each level.
Note: Your bonsais CP are calculated from the points of the four individual categories (Foliage, branches, trunk and roots). Besides your shaping skill, these are influenced through the nature of the bonsai.
Goal:
Grow a bonsai with 20 or more points in one of the individual categories
Tutorial: Patience skill
Instructions:
The longer you grow bonsais, the more you feel like being more patient in general.
You can now learn "Patience" a skill that lets you grow a bonsai over multiple level at once.
Goal:
Learn "Patience"
An open world
Instructions:
This is the current end of the game. Feel free to play further and try out the game, but there are no further tasks or mechanics to discover.
For now...
Goal:
Grow bonsais or go on more expeditions

Congratulations, you just reached your first skill level.
Every time you reach a skill level, new skills will be unlocked for you in the tab to learn. You also gain skill points from each skill level, which you will need to learn those new skills.
Have a look at the tab, maybe the new skills will be helpful for you.

Hello,
and welcome to the hobby of bonsai growing. I have heard that you are interested in growing your own bonsais and I can assist you with it.
To grow a bonsai, you will need a seedling first. You can get seedlings by going on expeditions. Do this by going to the tab and there .
You can call me sensei by the way.

Before going on an expedition, you can decide how long the expedition shall be.
Going on a longer expedition gives you the chance to find seedlings with a higher 'tree quality', an attribute that will become more important later on.
For now just do any length of expedition and then .

Going on more expeditions will give you the chance to find more seedlings with potentially different 'tree types'.
But first let's concentrate on growing your first bonsai. For that you first need to learn the art of 'tree styles' for bonsais. Go to the tab for that and learn the skill .

To learn a skill you need to fullfill certain requirements. In this case you need and the book .
Luckily I have both of these items and gladly give them to you, so that you can the skill right away.

Now that you have a seedling and the skills, we can plant your first bonsais.
To do that you can click on any of the ten free pot places on the left hand side as that is where your bonsais are being kept.

To plant and grow a bonsai, you first need to pick a seedling to plant.
Second, .
And lastly, the seedling.

Congratualtions on planting your first bonsai. Let me give you a short overview of your bonsai.
Your bonsai first of all consists of the tree type/quality that the seedling had as well as the style type that you chose.
Furthermore, your bonsai has a nature, which influences the potential of four tree attributes. These are: Foliage (), branches (), trunk () and roots ().
These attributes are then assigned attribute points (AP), either automatically or through your work on the bonsai and ulimately culminate in a base beauty (BB). I know it's a lot and we will come back to it later. I promise. For now let's concentrate on your further education.
You just unlocked your first milestone through planting this bonsai. Milestones give you experience and are a great way for you personally to grow as a bonsai master. Go to the tab next to see the milestones.

Under the tab you can both find your milestones, but also tasks that have been given to you. So far I have automatically finshed these for you, but the last task , I leave for you to finish.
I also added two more tasks for you: and . Finish these and we will continue our tour.

Well done on the tasks I gave you.
Once you grow more and more bonsais, it will be hard at one point to keep track on which you have grown and which not. For that the can help you.
What also can help you when growing more and more bonsais, is a bit of help. For that I added a task to your tab to learn the skill .
You can find the skill in your tab, though be advised you will need a book to learn it. You can buy the book under the tab.

Explain 'Shopping'-tab.
Furthermore you can also get a backpack here and go on other expedition which not only get you bonsais. I added a task to your list, which will help you with it.

Explain how you can also sell seedlings and bonsais or buy other items. Lead to 'Crafting'-tab and task to craft robot.

Explain how you can craft other things as well. Lead to 'Contest'-tab.

Explain 'Contest'-tab and task to participate in a contest.

Now it's up to you to become a bonsai master.
